@TITLE "MMURIP(1)ĀmanualĀpage"
 @{" " link "'#toc'/MAIN"}Table of Contents

 @{" " link "'#toc0'/MAIN"}Name mmurip - Extract samples from module @{" " link "'#toc1'/MAIN"}Synopsis @{"b"}mmurip@{"ub"} [@{"i"}generaloptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}outputoptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}qualityoptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}otheroptions@{"ui"}] [@{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"}] @{" " link "'#toc2'/MAIN"}Description @{"b"}mmurip@{"ub"} extracts samples from @{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"} or module from standard input if no @{"i"}MODFILE@{"ui"} is given. By default @{"b"}mmurip@{"ub"} extracts all samples to standard output as an single audio stream. if @{"b"}-p@{"ub"} or @{"b"}--sample@{"ub"} option is given, then only one sample will be extracted. if @{"b"}-B@{"ub"} or @{"b"}--batch@{"ub"} option is given then each sample will be extracted to separate file. 

When samples are extracted as an single stream or one of @{"i"}quality options@{"ui"} are given, the common quality parameters will be used for each sample, so that some or all output samples may be distorted. The quality parameters means the number of audio channels (mono or stereo) and the sample width (8 or 16 bit). 

When samples are extracted with @{"b"}-p@{"ub"} or @{"b"}--sample@{"ub"} and/or @{"b"}-B@{"ub"} or @{"b"}--batch@{"ub"} options and no @{"i"}qualityoptions@{"ui"} are given, each sample will have its own quality parameters that is identical to the quality parameters of the sample in the module, so that no sample distortion will be occur. 

@{"b"}mmurip@{"ub"} is part of the MikMod Utilities package, and uses MikMod Sound Library to load modules. @{" " link "'#toc3'/MAIN"}Exit Status @{"b"}mmurip@{"ub"} uses standard exit status, as defined in sysexits.h. See a description of all exit codes in @{" " link "'mmu.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu@{"ub"}(1) . @{" " link "'#toc4'/MAIN"}General Options See a description of all general options in @{" " link "'mmu.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu@{"ub"}(1) . @{" " link "'#toc5'/MAIN"}Output Options @{"b"}-o, --output=@{"ub"}@{"i"}FILE@{"ui"} Send the output data to @{"i"}FILE@{"ui"}. The default is to send data to standard output. This option cannot be combined with the @{"b"}-B@{"ub"} or @{"b"}--batch@{"ub"} option. @{"b"}-B, --batch@{"ub"} Extract samples to separate files. Output file names are identical to the module file name with suffix (extension) replaced with "_#" + suffix of output audio format, where "#" stands for the sample number. For example, first sample of "music.mod" will be written to "music_0.wav" file. If module is loaded from standard input, then output file names will be "stdin_#" + suffix of output audio format, where "#" stands for the sample number. This option cannot be combined with the @{"b"}-o@{"ub"} or @{"b"}--output@{"ub"} option. @{"b"}-t, --type=@{"ub"}@{"i"}TYPE@{"ui"} Specify output audio format. Specify @{"b"}help@{"ub"} as argument to get a list of all possible output audio formats. If audiofile support is not present (this is configured at compile-time), then only raw audio format is available, that is the raw audio data with no header information. The default is to use raw output format. @{" " link "'#toc6'/MAIN"}Quality Options @{"b"}-s, --stereo@{"ub"} Select stereo sound. @{"b"}-m, --mono@{"ub"} Select mono sound. @{"b"}-1, --16bit@{"ub"} Select 16 bit sound mode. @{"b"}-8, --8bit@{"ub"} Select 8 bit sound mode. @{" " link "'#toc7'/MAIN"}Other Options @{"b"}-r, --freq=@{"ub"}@{"i"}RATE@{"ui"} Specify the sample frequency, in hertz, that will be written to the header of output file(s). This option has no effect if output audio format is raw. The default is 44100 Hz. @{"b"}-p, --sample=@{"ub"}@{"i"}SMPNO@{"ui"} Extract only @{"i"}SMPNO@{"ui"} sample. The sample number is zero based (first sample have number 0, second 1, etc). Use @{" " link "'mmuinfo.1'/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmuinfo@{"ub"}(1) to get a list of all samples in the module. If this option is not given, then all samples from the module will be extracted. @{" " link "'#toc8'/MAIN"}Notes All defaults of @{"i"}quality options@{"ui"} can be changed at compile-time. To get information about compile-time configuration use @{"b"}mmu --version@{"ub"} command. 

When using the raw audio format the sample data is made of unsigned values in 8 bit sound mode, and signed little-endian values in 16 bit sound mode. @{" " link "'#toc9'/MAIN"}Bugs 8 bit signed samples after extracting take 8 bit unsigned. 16 bit unsigned samples after extracting take 16 bit signed. 16 bit big-endian samples after extracting take 16 bit little-endian. So if you want to get samples exactly as its stored in the module, use other tools (SOX for example) to convert samples to the preferred format. If you found any other bugs, please let me known. @{" " link "'#toc10'/MAIN"}Author Konstantin Korikov <lostclus@ua.fm> @{" " link "'#toc11'/MAIN"}See Also @{" " link "'mmu.guide/MAIN"}@{"b"}mmu(1) ,@{"ub"} 


